      8)  Motion (to impose requirements on the representation of bitfields)
          by Lajoie/Hartinger:
 
          Move we amend the WP by adding the following as a new paragraph
          after 9.6 [class.bit] paragraph 3:
 
          If the value true or false is stored into a bit-field of type bool
          of any size (including a one bit bit-field), the original bool value
          and the value of the bit-field shall compare equal.  If the value of
          an enumerator is stored into a bit-field of the same enumeration
          type and the number of bits in the bit-field is large enough to hold
          all the values of that enumeration type, the original enumerator
          value and the value of the bit-field shall compare equal.
 
      Motion passed X3J16: lots yes, 0 no.
      Motion passed WG21: 5 yes, 0 no, 1 abstain.
 
